chland":"Lüchow, Lüchow, Hanover, Prussia, Germany","Lüchow, Lüchow-Dannenberg, Lower Saxony, Germany":"Lüchow, Lüchow-Dannenberg, Lower Saxony, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Warpke","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Alfons.","German: from a pet form of any ancient Germanic personal name formed with <i>wer</i>, <i>war</i> + <i>berht</i>, <i>bald</i>, as in <i>Warmbold</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margarethe","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretha","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margarethe von Warpke was born about 1112, in Germany, her father, Graf Ulrich I. von Warpke, was 34 and her mother, Frau von Warpke, was 24. She had at least 1 son and 3 daughters with Graf Hermann von Lüchow I."},"et":{"um 1112–":"umbes 1112–Surnud","1112–Female":"1112–Surnud","1110–1174":"1110–1174","1130–1191":"1130–1191","1132–1185":"1132–1185","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1144–1184":"1144–1184","1080–1145":"1080–1145","1090–Female":"1090–Surnud","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1132":"1132","1110":"1110","1130":"1130","1185":"1185","1174":"1174","1184":"1184","1140":"1140","1191":"1191","um 1132":"umbes 1132","1145":"1145","1112":"1112","um 1140":"umbes 1140","1144":"1144","um 1112":"umbes 1112","Preußen, Deutschland":"Preußen, Saksamaa","Deutschland":"Saksamaa","Lüchow, Kreis Lüchow, Provinz Hannover, Preußen, Deutschland":"Lüchow, Kreis Lüchow, Provinz Hannover, Preußen, Saksamaa","Lüchow, Lüchow-Dannenberg, Lower Saxony, Germany":"Lüchow, Landkreis Lüchow-Dannenberg, Niedersachsen, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"um 1112–":"noin 1112–Kuollut","1112–Female":"1112–Kuollut","1110–1174":"1110–1174","1130–1191":"1130–1191","1132–1185":"1132–1185","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1144–1184":"1144–1184","1080–1145":"1080–1145","1090–Female":"1090–Kuollut","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1132":"1132","1110":"1110","1130":"1130","1185":"1185","1174":"1174","1184":"1184","1140":"1140","1191":"1191","um 1132":"noin 1132","1145":"1145","1112":"1112","um 1140":"noin 1140","1144":"1144","um 1112":"noin 1112","Preußen, Deutschland":"Pre